{"lemma":"خُلَّةٌ","slug":"خُلَّةٌ","root":"خ.ل.ل","root_slug":"خ-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خُلَّة","root":"خلل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11170"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gap, perforation, breach, gap even in canes or as large as a road"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dearth, need"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"peculiar trait, disposition, property","examples":[{"text":"الجُوذابات. أمّا المعمولة منها بالخبز فغذاؤها غذاء محمود والدم المتولّد منه دم جيّد لأنّها معمولة من خبز نضيج، وهي ملينة للطبيعة نافعة من خشومة قصة الرئة. وإن كانت باللبن والسكّر وماء النارجيل وعلّقت عليها بطّة سمينة أو دجاجة سمنة زادت في الباه زيادةً كثيرةً. والمعمولة بالحنطة غليطة بطيئة الهضم حارّة معطشة، والمعمولة بالأرزّ دونها في هذه الخلال. وكلّها كثير الغذاء بطيء النزول، ينبغي أن يستعان على هضمها بطول النوم وأن لا تؤكل هي إلا على جوعٍ صادق.","english":"al-jūḏābāt. When made from bread they are a laudably sustaining sustenance furthering the blood production for they are made from well-baked bread, and they are laxative and help against roughness of the windpipe, and if they are prepared with milk and sugar and coconut water and a fat duck or fatty chicken is hung above them then they add much to the libido. And made with wheat they are tough, slow in digestion, hot and causing thirst, whereas made with rice they are below these amiable properties. And all of them are sustaining and going down slowly; it is desired that one supports their digestion with long sleep and does not eat them except upon real hunger."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cordiality, amity, true friendship, affection","examples":[{"text":"يَا أَيُّهَا ٱلَّذِينَ آمَنُوا أَنْفِقُوا مِمَّا رَزَقْنَاكُم مِن قَبْلِ أَن يَأْتِيَ يَوْمٌ لَا بَيْعٌ فِيهِ وَلَا خُلَّةٌ وَلَا شَفَاعَةٌ","english":"O ye who believe! spend of that wherewith We have provided you ere a day come when there will be no trafficking, nor friendship, nor intercession. – Pickthall"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an opaque term used for any plant which is not حَمْض (ḥamḍ, “any saline, mostly a chenopodiaceous or zygophyllaceous plant”)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lace, toothpick, and the like instruments for picking"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"scabbard, case, wherewith for instance a sword is covered, and a thong fixed onto the extremity of a bow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"toothpickweed, Ammi gen. et spp."}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From خَلَّ (ḵalla, “to penetrate”). The Bedouinic term may be instead from خَلّ (ḵall, “vinegar”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11170","headword_ar":"خُلَّةٌ","root":"xl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. [or rather quasi-inf. n.] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAl~ahu","text_ar":"خَالَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.: (JK:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"True,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincere, friendship, love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affection;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluwlapN","text_ar":"خُلُولَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xulaAlapN","text_ar":"خُلَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaAlapN","text_ar":"خَلَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilaAlapN","text_ar":"خِلَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or all these signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a particular true"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincere friendship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affection, in which is no unsoundness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defect, and which may be chaste and may be vitious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K: [in which all are said to be substs., except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~apN","text_ar":"خُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though this were properly speaking an inf. n., though having a pl., as shown below:]) [and sometimes simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"friendship:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroHabN","text_ar":"مَرْحَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rHb","text_ar":"رحب"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~apN","text_ar":"خُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~apN","text_ar":"خَلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xil~N","text_ar":"خِلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xil~apN","text_ar":"خِلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", each with kesr, (K,) signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincere, friendship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and brotherly conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the last two as used in the phrases,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inahu","text_ar":"اـِنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lakariymu Alxil~i","text_ar":"لَكَرِيمُ الخِلِّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxil~api","text_ar":"الخِلَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is generous in respect of true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincere, friendship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (K:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~apN","text_ar":"خُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense explained above is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilaAlN","text_ar":"خِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliylN","text_ar":"خَلِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (JK, S, Msb, K;) namely, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sweet kind thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":": (JK:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any pasture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, that is not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"; all pasture, or herbage, consisting of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~ap","text_ar":"خُلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"being such as has in it saltness [or sourness]: (TA:) the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earofaj","text_ar":"عَرْفَج"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every tree that remains in winter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) accord. to Lh, it is [applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain kinds"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of trees &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to IAar,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peculiarly of trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but accord. to A'Obeyd, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shrubs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not including any great trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain thorny tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place of growth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place in which is a collection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of [the plants, or trees, called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earofaj","text_ar":"عَرْفَج"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any land not containing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the kind of plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AHn, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even though containing no plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xulalN","text_ar":"خُلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN xul~apN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ خُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araDuwna xulalN","text_ar":"اَرَضُونَ خُلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ISh says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~apN","text_ar":"خَلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xulalu AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"خُلَلُ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lands, in which is no"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sometimes containing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thorny trees such as are called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sometimes not containing such;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~apN","text_ar":"خُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land in which are no trees nor any herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) some say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~apN","text_ar":"خُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, which is the contrary of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":", has for a pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilaAlN","text_ar":"خِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and then, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilaAl","text_ar":"خِلَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"is formed the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axil~apN","text_ar":"اَخِلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and some say that this last means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage that is cut"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@jotuz~","text_ar":"وَا@جْتُزّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Auxotul~","text_ar":"اُخْتُلّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in which the latter verb seems to be an explicative adjunct to the former])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"while green."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 662, q. v.) They say that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~ap","text_ar":"خُلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the bread of camels, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"is their fruit, (JK, T, Sudot;, TA,) or their flesh-meat, (S, TA,) or their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyS","text_ar":"خَبِيص"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence, by way of comparison, it is applied to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repose; freedom from trouble"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inconvenience, and toil"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tranquillity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ampleness of circumstances:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":", to evil, and war: (T, TA:) and the former, to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, to death. (Ham p. 315.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Acid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sour, leaven"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ferment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","Msb","K","TA","AHn","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}